<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,871,1077]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,942,968]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Comments:</emphasis>
This species was first recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[768,849,943,969]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Florida</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Van Duzee, E. P." box="[894,1102,943,969]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref67052" refString="Van Duzee, E. P. (1904) Annotated list of the Pentatomidae recorded from America, north of Mexico, with descriptions of some new species. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 30 (1), 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1904">
<collectingRegion box="[894,938,943,969]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Van</collectingRegion>
Duzee (1904)
</bibRefCitation>
, who examined two different specimens collected at two different times (Slosson &amp; Uhler collections). 
<bibRefCitation author="Barber, H. G." box="[978,1136,979,1005]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="495 - 535" refId="ref44681" refString="Barber, H. G. (1914) Insects of Florida. II. Hemiptera. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 33, 495 - 535." type="journal article" year="1914">Barber (1914)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Blatchley, W. S." box="[1190,1379,979,1006]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref45712" refString="Blatchley, W. S. (1926) Heteroptera or True Bugs of Eastern North America with Special Reference to the Faunas of Indiana and Florida. The Nature Publishing Company, Indianapolis, Indiana, 1116 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6871" type="book" year="1926">Blatchley (1926)</bibRefCitation>
both reported additional new records from southern 
<collectingRegion box="[692,776,1015,1041]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Florida</collectingRegion>
, but we do not know of any new published records since 1926.
</paragraph>
